# UIUX.Web — clawbot deploy (detail)

**Hard rule (summary):** [`clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc`](clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc) — **alwaysApply.** UI changes are **not** complete without pull + **rebuild `web`** + restart + **in-container** proof + browser.

## Why `web` must be rebuilt

`UIUX.Web/Dockerfile` **COPY**s `dashboard.html`, `styles.css`, etc. into `/usr/share/nginx/html/`. `docker-compose.yml` mounts **only** `nginx/default.conf` into `web`; **HTML is not live-mounted from the repo.** After `git pull`, you **must** `docker compose build web`.

The **`api`** service mounts **`../:/repo`** — Python changes under `modules/` apply after pull + **restart `api`** without rebuilding the image (same bare image + pip).

## Commands (clawbot)

```bash
ssh jmiller@clawbot.a51.corp
cd ~/blackbox && git fetch origin main && git pull origin main && git rev-parse HEAD
cd ~/blackbox/UIUX.Web && docker compose build web && docker compose up -d web api
```

Then verify inside container (example):

```bash
cd ~/blackbox/UIUX.Web && docker compose exec web grep -q 'tc-scorecard-block' /usr/share/nginx/html/dashboard.html && echo OK
```

Operator URL (see `docker-compose.yml` / site): typically HTTPS on host; **hard refresh** after deploy.

## Do not claim “live for operator” without

Successful **pull**, **`build web`**, **up -d**, **in-container grep/curl**, and **browser confirmation** (or explicit operator sign-off).

